article.headline: Penn State 73, Arkansas State 61
article.story: ALBUQUERQUE, N.M. (AP) -- Seven-footer Jan Jagla scored 18 points and had 17 rebounds Sunday in Penn State's 73-61 win over Arkansas State in the first round of the Lobo Invitational. Penn State (5-4) never trailed as Ndu Egekeze scored the first 8 points for the Nittany Lions and Jagla took over in the second half. Arkansas State (8-2) was led by Tevoris Thompson with 19 points and Dewarick Spencer with 12 points and 10 rebounds. Jagla was a factor all over the court. He hit six of seven shots in the second half -- scoring 15 points -- including three 3-pointers. The Indians, who came into the tournament on a five-game winning streak, missed 16 of their first 17 shots and didn't get their second field goal of the game until J.J. Montgomery hit a layup with 7:20 left in the opening period. Montgomery, the Indians' second leading scorer with an average of more than 18 points a game, exemplified Arkansas State's shooting problems. The junior guard hit just two of 17 shots and was 1-for-8 on 3-pointers. Arkansas State was 7-of-36 overall on 3-point shots. Penn State also got solid games from Egekeze and Deforrest Riley. Egekeze finished with a season-high 15 points and 15 rebounds, while Deforrest scored 22 points, including five 3-pointers. Arkansas State, despite its poor shooting in the first half, took a 22-21 lead with 1:58 left in the half on a basket in the lane from Thompson. Penn State scored the final 6 points of the half, then used a 18-4 run in the first five minutes of the second half for a 45-26 lead with 14:46 left. Arkansas State got no closer than 10 points the rest of the way.
